{"type":"message","id":"f6e90c88","parentId":"8d20f9b9","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:21:37.259Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Executing Dota 2 Worker**\n\nI've verified the Dota 2 worker is active, which is great. Now, I'm setting up the news gathering process by running the `news_watcher.py` script for the various games. I'll also update the `MARKET_NEWS.md` file after. Next up, I need to figure out how to run the `news_watcher.py` script.\n\n\n**Initiating News Watcher**\n\nMy next action involves launching the `news_watcher.py` script for each game. I'm investigating how to execute the script; I'll ascertain whether it can be run directly or requires invocation with Python. After that, I will update the `MARKET_NEWS.md` file as specified.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771161697257_108","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/sentinel/news_watcher.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":56678,"output":120,"cacheRead":52947,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56798,"cost":{"input":0.113356,"output":0.00144,"cacheRead":0.0105894,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1253854}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771161691563}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7c0c85d","parentId":"f6e90c88","timestamp":"2026-02-15T13:21:37.277Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771161697257_108","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport requests\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nclass NewsWatcher:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.sources = [\n            \"https://store.steampowered.com/feeds/news/app/730/\",\n            \"https://store.steampowered.com/feeds/news/app/570/\",\n            \"https://store.steampowered.com/feeds/news/app/440/\",\n            \"https://store.steampowered.com/feeds/news/app/252490/\"\n        ]\n        self.keywords = [\"Update\", \"Operation\", \"Case\", \"Nerf\", \"Buff\"]\n        self.archive_file = \"docs_archive/MARKET_NEWS.md\"\n        \n        # Ensure archive dir exists\n        os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(self.archive_file), exist_ok=True)\n\n    def fetch_news(self):\n        found_news = []\n        print(\"Fetching news feeds...\")\n        \n        for url in self.sources:\n            try:\n                print(f\"Checking {url}...\")\n                response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n                if response.status_code == 200:\n                    root = ET.fromstring(response.content)\n                    # RSS structure: channel -> item -> title\n                    for item in root.findall('./channel/item'):\n                        title = item.find('title').text\n                        link = item.find('link').text\n                        pubDate = item.find('pubDate').text\n                        \n                        # Check keywords\n                        for keyword in self.keywords:\n                            if keyword.lower() in title.lower():\n                                found_news.append({\n                                    \"title\": title,\n                                    \"link\": link,\n                                    \"date\": pubDate,\n                                    \"keyword\": keyword\n                                })\n                                break # Only add once per item\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"Error fetching {url}: {e}\")\n                \n        return found_news\n\n    def update_archive(self, news_items):\n        if not news_items:\n            print(\"No significant news found.\")\n            return\n\n        with open(self.archive_file, \"a\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            for item in news_items:\n                entry = f\"- [{datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')}] **{item['keyword'].upper()} ALERT:** [{item['title']}]({item['link']}) ({item['date']})\\n\"\n                # Check if already exists to avoid dupes (simple check)\n                if not self._is_duplicate(entry):\n                    f.write(entry)\n                    print(f\"Logged: {item['title']}\")\n\n    def _is_duplicate(self, entry):\n        if not os.path.exists(self.archive_file):\n            return False\n        with open(self.archive_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            content = f.read()\n            return entry.strip() in content\n\n    def run(self):\n        print(\"Running News Sentinel...\")\n        news = self.fetch_news()\n        self.update_archive(news)\n        \n        if news:\n            print(f\"!!! PANIC MODE TRIGGERED !!! Update detected: {news[0]['title']}\")\n            print(f\"\\nLatest Headline: {news[0]['title']}\")\n            return news[0]['title']\n        else:\n            print(\"\\nNo major headlines found matching keywords.\")\n            return \"No news found.\"\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    watcher = NewsWatcher()\n    watcher.run()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771161697275}}
